thread.title: Red Bulls Clinch Top Seed
thread.title_full: Red Bulls Clinch Top Seed - The New York Times

author: The Associated Press
title: Red Bulls Clinch Top Seed
text:
Mike Grella scored seven seconds into the game — the fastest goal in M.L.S. history — and the host Red Bulls beat the Philadelphia Union, 4-1, to clinch the top seed in the Eastern Conference playoffs.
■ Nolito scored in the 90th minute, and Celta Vigo earned a 2-1 win at 10-man Villarreal to pull even with Real Madrid and Barcelona atop the Spanish league.
